A puppet module that manages the aptitude package manager for Ubuntu systems.


Purpose
=======

aptitude is the preferred package manager on ubuntu systems, but isn't
necessarily available by default. This puppet module ensures aptitude is
installed and contains an up-to-date package list.

Additionally, this module allows you to:

    - Automatically update all system packages (default: off).

Docs
====

To learn how to install and use puppet-aptitude, read our official
documentation: http://puppet-aptitude.rtfd.org/

